cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with an intuitionistic first-order prover and its integration into Coq, which is a proof assistant based on type theory and constructive logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as Coq is a programming language and proof assistant, and the paper proposes a method to generate sequent-style proofs from a certificate generated by the intuitionistic prover. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper proposes a method to integrate an external automated theorem prover with Coq, which can be useful in software verification and formal methods. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a method to generate certificates using a matrix characterization of intuitionistic first-order logic, which can be seen as a form of machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper deals with automated theorem proving and the integration of external provers, which are topics related to AI.
